their heart broken every day...

552
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:28,700
And I've been down that road!

553
00:37:28,740 --> 00:37:32,490
You've never even been
in the neighbourhood!

554
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:34,870
You're not even in love!

555
00:37:37,450 --> 00:37:38,620
You know what...

556
00:37:38,870 --> 00:37:40,120
Come.

557
00:37:42,120 --> 00:37:43,120
Lie down here.

558
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:45,910
- Alizeh, I'm not in the mood for sex...
- I'll slap you again!

559
00:37:46,620 --> 00:37:49,990
Lie down!

560
00:37:53,830 --> 00:37:54,950
Now...

561
00:37:57,330 --> 00:37:58,830
Does it hurt?

562
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:00,870
That's heartbreak.

563
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:02,740
Now?

564
00:38:02,910 --> 00:38:03,660
I'm okay.

565
00:38:03,870 --> 00:38:04,870
This is Lisa!

566
00:38:05,160 --> 00:38:08,780
Heartbreak!
Lisa!

567
00:38:08,870 --> 00:38:11,240
I understood, I've got it!

568
00:38:11,830 --> 00:38:12,660
Good!

569
00:38:12,990 --> 00:38:17,030
Now please go home!
The high must have worn off.

570
00:38:17,830 --> 00:38:21,530
This is Heartbreak Hotel, my friend...
You have to be qualified!

571
00:38:22,200 --> 00:38:25,660
You've driven me mad all night...
Go away!

572
00:39:28,740 --> 00:39:31,240
There she is... Ms. Gone Girl, herself.

573
00:39:34,410 --> 00:39:35,990
I'm sorry, Ayan...

574
00:39:37,450 --> 00:39:38,740
I truly am.

575
00:39:41,330 --> 00:39:42,830
Will you call me?

576
00:39:44,540 --> 00:39:46,990
No.

577
00:39:49,620 --> 00:39:51,330
Jesus be with you.

578
00:39:52,580 --> 00:39:53,870
Both of you.

579
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:03,700
Lisa!

580
00:40:04,830 --> 00:40:06,120
Ye evil shrew!

581
00:40:06,370 --> 00:40:07,450
Ye wayward wench!

582
00:40:07,700 --> 00:40:11,780
May thee be attack'd by
the fireth of a thousand suns!

583
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:17,870
Burneth, thee shrew! This is the
beshrew of a wrong'd mistress!

584
00:40:18,120 --> 00:40:19,120
Beshrew!

585
00:40:19,660 --> 00:40:20,530
Beshrew?

586
00:40:21,370 --> 00:40:22,200
What's that?

587
00:40:22,870 --> 00:40:23,660
Curse!

588
00:40:26,330 --> 00:40:27,410
Please don't curse me.

589
00:40:27,950 --> 00:40:29,370
Be gone, evil wench!

590
00:40:29,740 --> 00:40:32,830
If thee ev'r showeth thy face again,
thee shall be ruin'd!

591
00:40:38,240 --> 00:40:40,200
I'll help her with the bags.

592
00:40:40,700 --> 00:40:41,450
Are you crazy?!

593
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:43,870
Out of here, black-hearted wench!

594
00:40:45,330 --> 00:40:47,870
I've been dreaming of
talking like that for years!

595
00:40:47,950 --> 00:40:49,280
I'm having the best time!

596
00:40:52,370 --> 00:40:53,240
Now what?

597
00:40:53,910 --> 00:40:54,700
Now?

598
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:57,830
Now! Recovery Retreat!

599
00:40:58,660 --> 00:41:00,030
Recovery Retreat?

600
00:41:00,370 --> 00:41:03,740
Recovery Retreat!
Heartbreak Holiday, dude...

601
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:07,030
I told Dad that I've been
hurt because of him...

602
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:08,780
...now I need to go and recover!

603
00:41:09,200 --> 00:41:10,240
The plan is... Paris!

604
00:41:10,790 --> 00:41:12,490
What are you doing this weekend?

605
00:41:13,370 --> 00:41:15,990
I'm very busy... Classes,
appointments...

606
00:41:16,160 --> 00:41:17,530
Shuddap! You're free!

607
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:20,990
Tell your father...
I've kidnapped you.

608
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:36,160
Excited!

609
00:41:38,580 --> 00:41:40,200
Why are you so clingy?

610
00:42:03,290 --> 00:42:04,490
What's the rating of this place?

611
00:42:04,700 --> 00:42:06,490
5 stars! 3 for the hotel
and 2 for us!

612
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:10,580
1 you + 1 me equals 1 room?

613
00:42:11,120 --> 00:42:14,580
2 hotel rooms = over budget!

614
00:42:15,790 --> 00:42:17,240
What if you take advantage of me?!

615
00:42:17,830 --> 00:42:18,910
Shut up!

616
00:42:22,830 --> 00:42:24,530
Wow, nice!

617
00:42:24,830 --> 00:42:27,330
Yeah, man! I love hotel rooms!

618
00:42:30,620 --> 00:42:33,450
I wish I could live
in a hotel forever!

619
00:42:33,580 --> 00:42:34,870
Exactly!!

620
00:42:35,870 --> 00:42:38,580
New beds, new pillows!

621
00:42:38,740 --> 00:42:41,620
New soap, new shampoo! For free!

622
00:42:44,040 --> 00:42:45,120
Minibar!

623
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:47,530
That's not free!
You have to pay for it!

624
00:42:47,700 --> 00:42:49,200
And you know what the best part is?

625
00:42:49,540 --> 00:42:51,030
Room Service!!!

626
00:42:51,410 --> 00:42:53,160
I'll find a menu.

627
00:42:54,120 --> 00:42:55,580
Alizeh, have you ever
had paratha and eggs?

628
00:42:55,700 --> 00:42:56,950
Like you'll get that here!

629
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:58,240
No no...

630
00:43:00,450 --> 00:43:02,410
That feeling I get when I eat that...

631
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:06,870
I'm getting that feeling today...

632
00:43:07,870 --> 00:43:10,700
Like my heart is full.

633
00:43:11,160 --> 00:43:12,160
You know?

634
00:43:12,990 --> 00:43:15,740
I never want to lose this feeling.

635
00:43:18,580 --> 00:43:20,200
I know that feeling...

636
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:23,910
I feel like I'm
starring in my own film...

637
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:29,990
I want to dance, I want to sing,
I want to go crazy on the streets!

638
00:43:30,660 --> 00:43:32,990
Feeling hot, hot, hot...

639
00:43:34,580 --> 00:43:36,530
You think I'm nuts...

640
00:43:36,790 --> 00:43:39,410
No, dude... I've got
Bollywood in my blood, too.

641
00:43:39,830 --> 00:43:43,700
I want to wear saris
and run around mountains, too!

642
00:43:43,950 --> 00:43:46,080
The hills are alive...

643
00:43:46,660 --> 00:43:48,030
But you know what...

644
00:43:48,240 --> 00:43:50,950
I still have one
unrequited Bollywood dream...

645
00:43:51,080 --> 00:43:52,280
Which one?

646
00:43:52,540 --> 00:43:53,830
The airport dream.

647
00:43:55,990 --> 00:43:59,280
The airport dream. For so long
I dreamed that I would be that girl...

648
00:43:59,370 --> 00:44:02,620
...the one the boy chased through
the airport and confessed his love.

649
00:44:03,080 --> 00:44:04,490
Twice I thought he'd come...

650
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:07,450
Both times I waited for him...

651
00:44:08,080 --> 00:44:09,780
And both times, he didn't come.

652
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:13,740
Mademoiselle, we are Private Jet
people. We don't have airport dreams.

653
00:44:16,370 --> 00:44:18,580
We’re young,
we're free and you're in Paris...

654
00:44:18,660 --> 00:44:21,200
...with the future Mohd. Rafi!

655
00:44:22,240 --> 00:44:23,740
What's your point, dude?

656
00:44:34,240 --> 00:44:38,440
In this party, you're not the only gorgeous one

657
00:44:39,240 --> 00:44:42,440
Then why are you sulking all alone?

658
00:44:43,210 --> 00:44:47,750
On whom my heart, has become obsessed

659
00:44:48,350 --> 00:44:51,250
Is some Frenchie!!!

660
00:44:51,750 --> 00:44:55,750
If she agrees, then I'll take her in my arms

661
00:45:02,250 --> 00:45:05,250
When will you get such a chance again?

662
00:45:07,250 --> 00:45:10,250
Where will you find a heart like mine?

663
00:45:11,250 --> 00:45:15,250
Let me show you a colourful evening in Paris

664
00:45:16,250 --> 00:45:18,450
Look look look look look!!!!

665
00:45:56,870 --> 00:45:58,370
- Now?!
- Now what?

666
00:45:58,580 --> 00:45:59,700
Plan?

667
00:46:00,370 --> 00:46:01,530
Plan?!

668
00:46:02,580 --> 00:46:03,700
Wait for it...

669
00:46:24,870 --> 00:46:25,950
Oi, Hero!

670
00:46:26,990 --> 00:46:28,030
Come up!

671
00:46:28,330 --> 00:46:29,080
Help!

672
00:46:29,660 --> 00:46:31,490
Do you know how to tie a sari?

673
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:35,240
I know how to take it off...

674
00:46:37,040 --> 00:46:38,080
Disgusting...

675
00:46:38,330 --> 00:46:41,280
"Now, let's learn how
to tie a simple sari...

676
00:46:41,540 --> 00:46:45,870
'Ensure your petticoat
and blouse are matching...

677
00:46:46,450 --> 00:46:49,410
Now, this is how to
start draping a sari...

678
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:51,030
Okay?

679
00:46:51,160 --> 00:46:51,870
Okay...

680
00:46:53,040 --> 00:46:57,450
Alizeh, if I go around you again...
we'll have to get married!

681
00:46:58,200 --> 00:46:59,280
Just shut up.

682
00:47:15,790 --> 00:47:17,330
I'll slap you!

683
00:47:18,790 --> 00:47:24,700
Start pleating like so...
and tuck it in.

684
00:47:31,620 --> 00:47:33,410
Sexy...

685
00:47:34,950 --> 00:47:36,580
Not sexier than you...

686
00:47:41,370 --> 00:47:42,620
Shot's ready!

687
00:47:43,200 --> 00:47:44,740
And so am I!

688
00:47:53,580 --> 00:47:55,240
My morning prayer!

689
00:48:16,240 --> 00:48:23,240
There are sweet sweet words of love
on our lips...

690
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:31,240
As I walk ahead,
right behind is my love

691
00:48:50,250 --> 00:48:57,250
I wish my whole life
can be spent like this

692
00:48:58,250 --> 00:49:02,250
As I walk ahead,
right behind me is my love...

693
00:49:06,740 --> 00:49:08,330
Do you even see what I'm wearing?!

694
00:49:08,950 --> 00:49:10,200
Idiot!

695
00:49:12,370 --> 00:49:14,240
Get up now! Come on!

696
00:49:16,700 --> 00:49:18,660
Where's my jacket?

697
00:49:20,620 --> 00:49:21,830
You know, you're useless!

698
00:49:23,620 --> 00:49:26,410
Dude... Bollywood people are nuts!

699
00:49:27,160 --> 00:49:29,030
It's too freaking cold for romance!

700
00:49:30,040 --> 00:49:31,240
Come on in!

701
00:49:38,740 --> 00:49:41,830
You should be called Hennessey,
not Alizeh.

702
00:49:42,700 --> 00:49:43,990
Cognac's not really liquor.

703
00:49:44,240 --> 00:49:45,910
Of course it is! Give it here!

704
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:00,450
You really like me...

705
00:50:03,660 --> 00:50:05,410
You really like me.

706
00:50:06,410 --> 00:50:10,700
Like really, really, really like me.

707
00:50:11,240 --> 00:50:13,330
Don't lie... because I've noticed.

708
00:50:14,160 --> 00:50:14,830
Yeah...

709
00:50:15,450 --> 00:50:16,700
I really like you!

710
00:50:16,870 --> 00:50:18,660
Why? Quick, tell me.

711
00:50:19,790 --> 00:50:21,280
I don't know, man...

712
00:50:22,330 --> 00:50:23,740
The first time we met...

713
00:50:23,830 --> 00:50:25,660
...when we spent the night talking...

714
00:50:25,870 --> 00:50:32,410
I just got the feeling
that you're my friend...

715
00:50:33,330 --> 00:50:35,240
My best friend...

716
00:50:36,120 --> 00:50:37,580
...and always will be.

717
00:50:38,120 --> 00:50:39,120
I don't know...

718
00:50:45,490 --> 00:50:48,370
You know, I wasn't popular in school...

719
00:50:49,790 --> 00:50:52,870
They thought I was a weirdo,
freak, introverted...

720
00:50:53,540 --> 00:50:56,700
And honestly, it made no difference...

721
00:50:57,660 --> 00:50:58,740
You know why?

722
00:51:01,120 --> 00:51:05,080
Because I knew I was
holding on to my personality...

723
00:51:05,580 --> 00:51:08,410
I was waiting to find that one person...

724
00:51:08,790 --> 00:51:10,740
...who got my weirdness.

725
00:51:19,870 --> 00:51:22,280
So... best friend, huh?

726
00:51:23,870 --> 00:51:26,370
Bestest friend!

727
00:51:31,200 --> 00:51:32,990
And... you're not attracted to me?

728
00:51:36,080 --> 00:51:37,030
No...

729
00:51:44,370 --> 00:51:45,870
What's wrong?

730
00:51:48,950 --> 00:51:50,660
Ego's a bit bruised...

731
00:51:57,740 --> 00:52:01,700
Are you attracted?

732
00:52:02,830 --> 00:52:03,530
Like...

733
00:52:04,620 --> 00:52:05,450
...a lot?

734
00:52:06,870 --> 00:52:10,490
Not a lot... But... yeah I am.

735
00:52:18,790 --> 00:52:21,410
Don’t feel weird...
I don't love you or anything.

736
00:52:21,910 --> 00:52:23,700
No, no... I know that.

737
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:31,910
You know,
I'm really happy we're friends...

738
00:52:33,410 --> 00:52:39,620
I feel that sometimes
lust just kills friendship...

739
00:52:41,080 --> 00:52:43,080
Love is passion...

740
00:52:43,910 --> 00:52:46,370
...but friendship is peace.

741
00:52:48,580 --> 00:52:52,910
And I never, ever want
to lose the peace between us.

742
00:52:53,740 --> 00:52:55,910
Girlfriend, boyfriend, husband, wife...

743
00:52:56,370 --> 00:52:59,830
... when those relationships die...
the people just leave.

744
00:53:02,040 --> 00:53:07,870
And I never want to leave you, Ayan...

745
00:53:10,240 --> 00:53:12,080
- Never?
- Never.

746
00:53:17,080 --> 00:53:18,990
Wow, I feel all mushy...

747
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:24,240
What do I do?

748
00:53:24,540 --> 00:53:25,490
Go ahead...

749
00:53:26,370 --> 00:53:28,240
I'm feeling a little mushy, myself...

750
00:53:29,490 --> 00:53:30,830
Give me a hug...

751
00:53:59,240 --> 00:54:00,450
I've decided that...

752
00:54:00,620 --> 00:54:01,580
What?

753
00:54:01,830 --> 00:54:04,950
I've decided we're
staying here another week!

754
00:54:05,450 --> 00:54:10,200
Oh, no... I'm really busy...
Meetings, appointments...

755
00:54:10,410 --> 00:54:12,280
Shuddap! You're free!

756
00:54:12,540 --> 00:54:13,490
Okay, I am!

757
00:54:13,700 --> 00:54:16,370
- So good?
- Yes, poopie! Yes!

758
00:54:18,200 --> 00:54:22,700
Can we get two beers and
something to eat... like peanuts...

759
00:54:23,040 --> 00:54:25,240
Peanuts... you know, peanuts?

760
00:54:25,870 --> 00:54:28,030
Kidding... just beer, please!

761
00:54:28,290 --> 00:54:29,910
Stop staring and pay!

762
00:55:52,290 --> 00:55:55,120
Ayan, I need to go...

763
00:55:56,540 --> 00:55:58,200
I need to get out of here...

764
00:55:59,160 --> 00:56:01,080
You can stay if you want,
I just need to go.

765
00:56:01,240 --> 00:56:02,780
One sec, I'll organize the plane...

766
00:56:02,870 --> 00:56:05,700
I'll walk home if l have to,
I just need to go right now!

767
00:56:11,410 --> 00:56:13,240
Where's my stuff?

768
00:56:25,120 --> 00:56:27,120
This room is such a mess...

769
00:56:28,620 --> 00:56:30,080
Alizeh are you okay?

770
00:56:30,790 --> 00:56:32,450
Alizeh... are you alright?

771
00:56:32,830 --> 00:56:33,620
Are you okay, Alizeh?

772
00:56:33,790 --> 00:56:36,580
I'm fine, Ayan! Just stop- I'm fine!

773
00:56:37,080 --> 00:56:40,580
I'm fine!

774
00:56:46,660 --> 00:56:48,030
He can't come back...

775
00:56:49,990 --> 00:56:51,450
I don't want to see him.

776
00:56:52,120 --> 00:56:56,950
He was gone.
I erased every trace of him...

777
00:56:57,450 --> 00:57:02,280
He can't come back,
do you understand?

778
00:57:29,490 --> 00:57:32,740
Yeah, Captain...
Terminal FBO 4, right?

779
00:57:34,490 --> 00:57:36,870
Okay... 45 minutes.

780
00:57:37,290 --> 00:57:38,490
Thank you so much!

781
00:57:38,790 --> 00:57:40,660
Alizeh... Alizeh!

782
00:57:40,870 --> 00:57:42,870
Sir, please!
She doesn't want to talk to you!

783
00:57:43,160 --> 00:57:44,450
Who the hell is this?
Your lover?

784
00:57:44,540 --> 00:57:46,080
- I'm her friend.
- I wasn't speaking to you!

785
00:57:46,160 --> 00:57:47,450
Well, she doesn't
want to speak to you!

786
00:57:47,540 --> 00:57:50,240
Stay out of it, man!
This is between us!

787
00:57:51,540 --> 00:57:52,330
Sir, please!

788
00:57:52,490 --> 00:57:53,780
- Hands off!
- Or else?

789
00:57:53,910 --> 00:57:55,660
Stop it! Stop it!

790
00:57:58,790 --> 00:57:59,780
Stop it!

791
00:58:05,370 --> 00:58:06,950
I love you, Alizeh...

792
00:58:10,080 --> 00:58:11,160
Come on, Alizeh.

793
00:58:11,660 --> 00:58:14,530
I know I made mistakes, but
how much longer will you punish me...

794
00:58:17,700 --> 00:58:21,080
You can't just cut me out
of your life after all these years...

795
00:58:32,080 --> 00:58:34,870
Come on, let's go...

796
00:58:35,620 --> 00:58:38,660
Alizeh, please give me a chance...

797
00:58:39,160 --> 00:58:40,330
Ayan...

798
00:58:42,950 --> 00:58:43,870
Go.

799
00:58:46,870 --> 00:58:47,830
Go...

800
00:58:50,160 --> 00:58:52,660
Okay, I'm right here... I'll wait...

801
00:58:52,950 --> 00:58:54,080
No, Ayan...

802
00:58:54,790 --> 00:58:55,910
Go...

803
00:58:57,040 --> 00:58:58,030
To London?

804
00:59:03,660 --> 00:59:05,580
Alizeh, the plane
won't come back for you...

805
00:59:07,870 --> 00:59:09,330
I'll find my way...

806
00:59:11,540 --> 00:59:12,330
Okay...

807
00:59:16,740 --> 00:59:17,780
Take care.

808
00:59:44,540 --> 00:59:47,080
Ever been suddenly slapped?

809
00:59:49,410 --> 00:59:50,990
That's love.

810
00:59:52,490 --> 00:59:55,740
And it only hits you harder,
when there's someone else involved...

811
00:59:58,410 --> 01:00:00,580
Why is there ever someone else?

812
01:00:12,580 --> 01:00:14,080
- Hello?
- Ayan?

813
01:00:14,490 --> 01:00:16,200
Alizeh! Hi!

814
01:00:16,660 --> 01:00:19,120
Where are you?

815
01:00:19,580 --> 01:00:22,530
Where are you?!
I've been calling you for days!

816
01:00:22,700 --> 01:00:26,120
Please leave a message
after the tone...

817
01:00:26,240 --> 01:00:28,280
Please leave a message...
Even your voicemail's full!

818
01:00:28,450 --> 01:00:29,990
Where are you?!

819
01:00:30,700 --> 01:00:31,660
In Lucknow...

820
01:00:32,290 --> 01:00:34,660
Lucknow...why?

821
01:00:35,120 --> 01:00:36,700
I'm here with Ali...

822
01:00:39,290 --> 01:00:40,780
Ali... Right...

823
01:00:41,830 --> 01:00:43,080
Same flight...

824
01:00:43,540 --> 01:00:45,280
Passenger seat...

825
01:00:45,870 --> 01:00:47,490
Together... Same plane?

826
01:00:47,580 --> 01:00:51,370
- What are you saying?!
I'm with Ali...

827
01:00:52,490 --> 01:00:53,450
Did you sleep with him?

828
01:00:53,660 --> 01:00:54,830
- Ayan! What?!

829
01:00:55,700 --> 01:00:56,780
Don't lie to me...

830
01:00:57,120 --> 01:00:58,080
I know you had sex with him.

831
01:00:58,790 --> 01:01:00,280
He's your lover now...

832
01:01:00,700 --> 01:01:01,580
Boyfriend...

833
01:01:01,740 --> 01:01:02,780
Back together...

834
01:01:03,040 --> 01:01:04,620
Are you drunk?!

835
01:01:04,740 --> 01:01:06,080
You're the one who's drunk!

836
01:01:07,040 --> 01:01:10,450
You said you never
wanted to see him again!

837
01:01:11,200 --> 01:01:12,700
I know, Ayan...

838
01:01:13,870 --> 01:01:15,910
But people in love are liars.

839
01:01:16,080 --> 01:01:18,330
This isn't love... it's weakness!

840
01:01:18,830 --> 01:01:20,700
Ali's my weakness...

841
01:01:22,990 --> 01:01:27,620
Alizeh, he's going to leave you.

842
01:01:28,330 --> 01:01:30,370
Then don't call me...
I'm very busy!

843
01:01:31,120 --> 01:01:32,660
I know you're being protective...

844
01:01:32,870 --> 01:01:34,410
You're a goddamn fraud!

845
01:01:34,620 --> 01:01:36,030
Fake! Liar!

846
01:01:36,790 --> 01:01:39,450
You can say what you want...

847
01:01:40,620 --> 01:01:42,740
But I love him...

848
01:01:43,200 --> 01:01:46,120
- I can't help it...
I really love him.

849
01:01:46,660 --> 01:01:48,660
- He's very sorry...

850
01:01:48,910 --> 01:01:49,740
- He even cried!

851
01:01:49,830 --> 01:01:51,530
But Alizeh, I cry all the time...

852
01:01:52,870 --> 01:01:54,870
Where do you fit
in to all of this?!

853
01:01:55,290 --> 01:01:56,030
Yeah...

854
01:01:56,620 --> 01:01:58,160
What does it have to do with me?

855
01:01:58,660 --> 01:02:01,080
Ayan, listen... It's important.

856
01:02:01,660 --> 01:02:05,280
Ali's going on tour for a year...
and he wants me to go with him.

857
01:02:05,910 --> 01:02:08,200
- He wants to marry me and...

858
01:02:08,450 --> 01:02:10,200
- ...he proposed.

859
01:02:10,700 --> 01:02:12,080
What did you say...

860
01:02:12,580 --> 01:02:13,870
- Yes, what else?!

861
01:02:14,990 --> 01:02:18,410
- Mum and Dad have kicked me out...

862
01:02:18,620 --> 01:02:22,780
- ...they won't come for
the wedding, either...

863
01:02:23,580 --> 01:02:25,830
- Some of Ali's useless cousins
will be at the wedding...

864
01:02:26,700 --> 01:02:29,950
- Will you come from my side...
For me?

865
01:02:32,290 --> 01:02:33,950
I don't have a visa...

866
01:02:34,240 --> 01:02:37,080
- Yo, Mr. Britain!
I'll organize all of that...

867
01:02:37,700 --> 01:02:39,830
- So... You'll come?

868
01:02:41,490 --> 01:02:42,740
Hello? Ayan?

869
01:02:43,870 --> 01:02:44,830
Ayan?

870
01:02:46,240 --> 01:02:47,620
Of course I will!

871
01:02:47,790 --> 01:02:49,620
Thank you, man...

872
01:02:50,620 --> 01:02:51,910
- Dude, I love you...

873
01:02:52,200 --> 01:02:53,780
- Say congratulations!

874
01:03:28,900 --> 01:03:31,400
There is no other Punjabi girl

875
01:03:31,600 --> 01:03:34,070
like you in the village, O dear one

876
01:03:34,400 --> 01:03:37,300
Why do you feel shy, sitting near the window?

877
01:03:37,710 --> 01:03:40,810
Be visible on the patio, O dear one

878
01:03:59,410 --> 01:04:02,910
O bride-to-be, your style is very fantastic

879
01:04:03,410 --> 01:04:06,610
You give orders on social media

880
01:04:07,410 --> 01:04:09,810
You talk on the phone with your left hand...

881
01:04:11,010 --> 01:04:13,810
...and apply henna on your right hand!

882
01:04:33,210 --> 01:04:36,210
You don't worry about your boyfriend

883
01:04:36,710 --> 01:04:38,910
and say 'Okay, bye' on the first date itself!

884
01:04:39,610 --> 01:04:43,910
The poor guy feels sad like Devdas,

885
01:04:44,400 --> 01:04:46,910
and then you smile and make an innocent face.

886
01:04:47,410 --> 01:04:54,110
Cutie pie, cutie pie...

887
01:04:55,420 --> 01:05:01,420
Oh my... cutie pie...

888
01:05:18,420 --> 01:05:20,920
You're going to parties wearing perfume,

889
01:05:21,820 --> 01:05:25,220
is an old way of luring the guys...

890
01:05:25,420 --> 01:05:29,220
You touch all the chords of body and soul,

891
01:05:29,420 --> 01:05:33,220
play flute without even touching it to your mouth.

892
01:05:33,420 --> 01:05:36,820
It's okay to steal the sleep of the young guys,

893
01:05:37,230 --> 01:05:40,300
But why do you increase the blood pressure of the old ones?!

894
01:05:40,430 --> 01:05:42,430
You have no worries regarding your boyfriend!

895
01:05:43,430 --> 01:05:46,430
You end the first date itself by saying 'Ok, bye!'

896
01:05:47,430 --> 01:05:50,230
Like Devdas, he cries...

897
01:05:51,430 --> 01:05:54,430
While you laugh and make an innocent face

898
01:05:58,430 --> 01:06:04,430
Cutie Pie...Cutie Pie...

899
01:06:33,540 --> 01:06:34,990
Hi, bro!

900
01:06:46,240 --> 01:06:47,780
Alizeh...

901
01:06:48,240 --> 01:06:49,410
Weds...

902
01:06:51,450 --> 01:06:52,450
Ayan!

903
01:07:28,290 --> 01:07:31,660
Ayan!
You're spinning like a top!

904
01:07:37,850 --> 01:07:39,700
Okay, I'll leave now...

905
01:07:39,700 --> 01:07:42,700
...remember me in your prayers

906
01:07:43,200 --> 01:07:45,550
Keep the taste of my intention...

907
01:07:45,700 --> 01:07:48,710
...on your tongue

908
01:07:54,150 --> 01:07:56,000
Okay, I'll leave now...

909
01:07:56,000 --> 01:07:59,000
...remember me in your prayers

910
01:07:59,100 --> 01:08:01,850
Keep the taste of my intention...

911
01:08:02,000 --> 01:08:04,210
...on your tongue

912
01:08:04,700 --> 01:08:06,910
Keep my good deeds...

913
01:08:07,210 --> 01:08:09,210
...in the corners of your heart

914
01:08:09,700 --> 01:08:12,210
And keep my greetings close to you...

915
01:08:12,410 --> 01:08:15,210
even in my letters & telegrams

916
01:08:15,710 --> 01:08:20,210
I have taken your darkness,

917
01:08:20,300 --> 01:08:25,800
and my bright shining star is yours now.

918
01:08:26,010 --> 01:08:28,500
O my moon...

919
01:08:28,800 --> 01:08:31,100
O my dearest moon...

920
01:08:31,600 --> 01:08:33,900
O my beloved moon...

921
01:08:34,000 --> 01:08:36,200
O my beloved!

922
01:09:29,660 --> 01:09:32,830
You're seriously like Mohd. Rafi!

923
01:09:33,990 --> 01:09:36,030
I was wrong about you, man!

924
01:09:36,240 --> 01:09:38,030
You really can sing!

925
01:09:41,410 --> 01:09:45,330
Forget this MBA...
Follow your dreams!

926
01:09:45,660 --> 01:09:48,030
Not like you can't afford to!

927
01:09:48,290 --> 01:09:49,700
Today you sang with such...

928
01:09:49,790 --> 01:09:50,950
Pain?

929
01:10:02,160 --> 01:10:03,410
Love?

930
01:10:05,040 --> 01:10:05,950
Ayan...

931
01:10:06,580 --> 01:10:07,910
Tell me, Alizeh...

932
01:10:08,490 --> 01:10:11,660
Did I sing with pain & love today?

933
01:10:15,160 --> 01:10:16,490
Who was it for?

934
01:10:20,540 --> 01:10:21,910
Who was it for?

935
01:10:22,990 --> 01:10:24,330
Should I tell you?

936
01:10:25,290 --> 01:10:26,910
- No...
- But you must know.

937
01:10:28,450 --> 01:10:30,240
I love you, Alizeh.

938
01:10:32,200 --> 01:10:33,410
I love you...

939
01:10:34,240 --> 01:10:36,280
I'm madly in love with you.

940
01:10:39,700 --> 01:10:43,200
And now, it's too late...

941
01:10:49,540 --> 01:10:54,660
Now, I want that DJ Ali
to die in the wedding procession...

942
01:10:55,620 --> 01:10:58,490
And from that shock,
I want you to die, too.

943
01:11:01,490 --> 01:11:04,240
If I can't have you, no one can.

944
01:11:06,910 --> 01:11:09,120
Ayan... Please...

945
01:11:09,370 --> 01:11:10,910
Please, Ayan!

946
01:11:13,540 --> 01:11:15,780
You want to know what it feels like?!

947
01:11:20,700 --> 01:11:21,910
I'll show you...

948
01:11:22,290 --> 01:11:23,620
Ayan!

949
01:11:25,240 --> 01:11:36,370
Alizeh...

950
01:11:36,490 --> 01:11:37,990
Alizeh!

951
01:11:44,490 --> 01:11:48,410
May death not come til you part, Mrs. DJ Ali...

952
01:11:49,410 --> 01:11:50,950
Have a great life...

953
01:11:52,450 --> 01:11:53,910
It's all good.

954
01:11:55,910 --> 01:12:01,610
Beloved...

955
01:12:03,610 --> 01:12:08,610
O beloved

956
01:12:08,700 --> 01:12:11,200
O my moon...

957
01:12:11,200 --> 01:12:13,510
O my moon...

958
01:12:14,210 --> 01:12:19,910
O my beloved moon...

959
01:12:29,920 --> 01:12:43,500
I am turning my path away from your direction...

960
01:12:45,100 --> 01:12:55,420
I am a sandlewood leaving my fragrance with you...

961
01:12:56,150 --> 01:13:07,050
...leaving my heart's desires under your pillow

962
01:13:09,120 --> 01:13:24,210
This nomad wraps the cotton cloth of an ascetic and goes...

963
01:13:34,210 --> 01:13:37,210
O my beloved...

964
01:14:23,910 --> 01:14:25,160
May I sit here?

965
01:14:25,370 --> 01:14:27,200
My wife's sitting there.

966
01:14:29,620 --> 01:14:31,030
I don't see anyone.

967
01:14:35,790 --> 01:14:37,030
Excuse me, ma'am...

968
01:14:38,450 --> 01:14:39,830
May I sit there?

969
01:14:43,160 --> 01:14:44,580
Yeah, sure...

970
01:14:45,660 --> 01:14:46,990
Thank you.

971
01:14:51,200 --> 01:14:52,200
Hello!

972
01:14:52,950 --> 01:14:53,780
Hello.

973
01:14:55,200 --> 01:14:56,450
Grapes?

974
01:15:03,240 --> 01:15:05,580
There are a lot of empty seats...

975
01:15:09,490 --> 01:15:11,080
But I don't want to be alone.

976
01:15:15,330 --> 01:15:16,620
I was at a wedding...

977
01:15:16,790 --> 01:15:18,240
My best friend's wedding!

978
01:15:20,160 --> 01:15:21,830
I left that halfway.

979
01:15:23,450 --> 01:15:24,870
Book or the wedding?

980
01:15:27,200 --> 01:15:28,280
Both...

981
01:15:33,040 --> 01:15:37,490
British Passport!

982
01:15:38,290 --> 01:15:40,990
I was born in England. You too?

983
01:15:42,740 --> 01:15:44,120
Same pinch...

984
01:15:44,620 --> 01:15:48,120
I'm on my way to
Frankfurt...Via Dubai.

985
01:15:49,620 --> 01:15:50,580
You?

986
01:15:50,830 --> 01:15:51,990
Vienna.

987
01:15:52,620 --> 01:15:53,740
Via Dubai?

988
01:15:56,160 --> 01:15:57,780
Same pinch!

989
01:16:00,330 --> 01:16:03,450
So what's up?
What do you do?

990
01:16:05,490 --> 01:16:06,740
Write.

991
01:16:07,450 --> 01:16:10,160
Nice to meet you, Ms. Wright.
I'm Ayan.

992
01:16:11,080 --> 01:16:12,490
I write poetry.

993
01:16:15,200 --> 01:16:16,580
Oh!

994
01:16:25,370 --> 01:16:26,830
Too good...

995
01:16:27,160 --> 01:16:28,410
We'll chat on the flight...

996
01:16:28,620 --> 01:16:31,620
Wait 'til you hear
some of my stories...

997
01:16:31,950 --> 01:16:33,200
What's up?

998
01:16:34,950 --> 01:16:37,080
Chatter is a fool's pursuit.

999
01:16:37,870 --> 01:16:41,780
Your eyes can't hide
what your words conceal.

1000
01:16:47,160 --> 01:16:51,990
Why hide your tears when, without permission, they don't fall?

1001
01:16:55,240 --> 01:16:56,910
Don't imprison them...

1002
01:16:57,290 --> 01:16:58,950
Let them be free...

1003
01:17:15,040 --> 01:17:16,450
I'm very sad...

1004
01:17:52,580 --> 01:17:53,620
Thanks for listening...

1005
01:17:53,700 --> 01:17:56,620
And sorry... I think...
I fell asleep, talking.

1006
01:17:56,910 --> 01:17:58,490
Well, you were even
talking in your sleep...

1007
01:17:58,660 --> 01:18:00,160
Shit! What did I say?

1008
01:18:05,080 --> 01:18:06,120
Ayan...

1009
01:18:06,580 --> 01:18:09,740
I know words can't always
heal scars that run so deep...

1010
01:18:10,410 --> 01:18:12,950
But words are all I have...

1011
01:18:13,240 --> 01:18:15,620
So here, this is for you!

1012
01:18:16,290 --> 01:18:18,240
I hope it helps a little...

1013
01:18:18,490 --> 01:18:21,120
And if words aren't your thing...

1014
01:18:21,580 --> 01:18:23,200
Maybe the number will help.

1015
01:19:28,490 --> 01:19:32,580
People always say
heart over mind...

1016
01:19:33,290 --> 01:19:35,240
But when the heart breaks...

1017
01:19:36,200 --> 01:19:38,910
Shouldn't you follow your mind?

1018
01:19:49,910 --> 01:19:51,120
Hello?

1019
01:19:51,290 --> 01:19:54,280
- Chatter is a fool's
pursuit... or so I've heard...

1020
01:19:54,450 --> 01:19:56,660
- But old habits die hard...

1021
01:19:57,540 --> 01:20:00,370
I've been rather
impatient for this call...

1022
01:20:05,740 --> 01:20:06,740
Hello?

1023
01:20:07,200 --> 01:20:09,030
Sorry, my cheeks are turning pink...

1024
01:20:09,370 --> 01:20:12,120
You make me blush...

1025
01:20:13,660 --> 01:20:15,580
It's true, though...

1026
01:20:15,830 --> 01:20:19,160
You've told me
everything about you...

1027
01:20:19,370 --> 01:20:21,740
...and you know nothing about me...

1028
01:20:23,540 --> 01:20:25,660
- Why do you think I'm here?
- Where?

1029
01:20:26,620 --> 01:20:27,660
Vienna...

1030
01:20:28,040 --> 01:20:30,330
What are you doing here?

1031
01:20:31,080 --> 01:20:33,200
Crossed the boundary
to cross some boundaries...

1032
01:20:35,040 --> 01:20:36,530
That's tough...

1033
01:20:36,740 --> 01:20:39,370
- I can handle tough...

1034
01:20:39,620 --> 01:20:43,200
Get to work, then...
See you tonight at 8?

1035
01:20:43,290 --> 01:20:44,330
- I'll send you the address...

1036
01:20:44,410 --> 01:20:46,030
Okay... Of your house, right?

1037
01:20:46,240 --> 01:20:47,450
You wish...

1038
01:23:33,870 --> 01:23:35,030
Good morning...

1039
01:23:35,120 --> 01:23:36,120
Morning...

1040
01:23:36,200 --> 01:23:37,580
Slept well?

1041
01:23:37,790 --> 01:23:38,870
Hmm...

1042
01:23:39,540 --> 01:23:42,490
I made breakfast for myself,
I hope you don't mind...

1043
01:23:43,740 --> 01:23:45,620
I'd have made you some...

1044
01:23:45,990 --> 01:23:48,080
But I didn't know
what you'd like.

1045
01:23:48,290 --> 01:23:50,450
You know nothing about me.

1046
01:23:51,080 --> 01:23:52,660
I got to know quite
a bit last night...

1047
01:23:52,740 --> 01:23:55,620
Passion isn't familiarity...

1048
01:23:57,700 --> 01:23:59,870
I'm blushing again...

1049
01:24:01,540 --> 01:24:02,990
Change of topic!

1050
01:24:03,330 --> 01:24:05,200
I read some of your poetry...

1051
01:24:06,910 --> 01:24:08,240
It's beautiful.

1052
01:24:13,540 --> 01:24:16,490
Glad you liked them...

1053
01:24:16,910 --> 01:24:20,450
I don't get much
appreciation for my poetry...

1054
01:24:22,080 --> 01:24:24,580
There's so much angst
in your poems...

1055
01:24:26,370 --> 01:24:29,080
Angst will always find angst...

1056
01:24:29,450 --> 01:24:31,700
Can I steal it for my music?

1057
01:24:33,660 --> 01:24:35,870
Careful...
I have an excellent lawyer...

1058
01:24:35,950 --> 01:24:38,200
He didn't even spare
my ex-husband!

1059
01:24:38,540 --> 01:24:40,080
Divorced!

1060
01:24:40,330 --> 01:24:41,780
Why so pleased?

1061
01:24:42,040 --> 01:24:43,620
Of course!
You're single...

1062
01:24:44,370 --> 01:24:45,530
Happily divorced...

1063
01:24:46,120 --> 01:24:47,450
...and I have no regrets...

1064
01:24:47,700 --> 01:24:50,160
Tahir and I are
very good friends.

1065
01:24:50,870 --> 01:24:53,160
Every poetess should
marry at least once...

1066
01:24:53,450 --> 01:24:56,740
A happy marriage means
a good life...

1067
01:24:57,540 --> 01:25:00,870
...an unhappy one means
good poetry!

1068
01:25:02,290 --> 01:25:03,780
By the way, I was kidding...

1069
01:25:03,910 --> 01:25:06,870
If you need my poetry...
Go ahead.

1070
01:25:07,740 --> 01:25:09,120
Thanks...

1071
01:25:09,660 --> 01:25:11,660
...but what I need is you.

1072
01:25:13,160 --> 01:25:15,330
I don't want to be needed...

1073
01:25:16,040 --> 01:25:17,660
I want to be desired.

1074
01:25:24,330 --> 01:25:26,370
You're relentless...

1075
01:25:26,620 --> 01:25:27,870
Like a walking-talking Ghalib...

1076
01:25:27,950 --> 01:25:29,410
...what am I supposed to say?

1077
01:25:30,740 --> 01:25:32,990
Your silence said
more than enough...

1078
01:25:33,990 --> 01:25:34,990
Don't worry...

1079
01:25:35,620 --> 01:25:37,910
l have no room for
a relationship in my life...

1080
01:25:39,200 --> 01:25:40,490
Not anymore...

1081
01:25:42,370 --> 01:25:44,580
There’s more than
one kind of relationship...

1082
01:25:46,040 --> 01:25:48,660
...but only if you're up for it.

1083
01:25:51,790 --> 01:25:53,660
What are the rules like?

1084
01:25:54,040 --> 01:25:55,780
Easily broken...

1085
01:25:58,370 --> 01:26:00,410
So you get my poetry...

1086
01:26:00,910 --> 01:26:02,950
The chance to drown your sorrows...

1087
01:26:05,240 --> 01:26:06,280
What do I get?

1088
01:26:08,370 --> 01:26:09,990
I thought I was enough.

1089
01:26:38,900 --> 01:26:43,300
The bird of my soul writhes in pain

1090
01:26:44,300 --> 01:26:48,300
But it's unable to find the island of peace

1091
01:26:49,300 --> 01:26:54,300
What should I do? What should I do?!!

1092
01:26:55,310 --> 01:26:59,310
Just for once, show yourself God

1093
01:27:00,310 --> 01:27:05,310
Give me some hope even if it's false

1094
01:27:06,310 --> 01:27:10,310
What should I do? What should I do?!

1095
01:27:10,610 --> 01:27:14,110
Bulleya, friend of Ranjha

1096
01:27:14,310 --> 01:27:16,310
Listen to my call, Bulleya

1097
01:27:17,310 --> 01:27:19,310
You are my only friend, Bulleya

1098
01:27:20,310 --> 01:27:22,310
You are my guide, my guardian

1099
01:27:22,310 --> 01:27:24,310
Your destination, O crazy one...

1100
01:27:25,310 --> 01:27:27,310
...is across the border

1101
01:27:28,310 --> 01:27:30,310
O our caretaker, Bulleya

1102
01:27:31,320 --> 01:27:33,320
You're my guardian, my guide

1103
01:28:06,320 --> 01:28:11,310
I'm just an immigrant like
a butterfly hugging Kabul

1104
01:28:12,320 --> 01:28:16,320
I stay for one moment & fly away in another

1105
01:28:18,320 --> 01:28:23,320
I'm on the path that is searching for heaven

1106
01:28:24,320 --> 01:28:28,320
Where you turn, I turn with you

1107
01:28:29,320 --> 01:28:33,320
I want to be part of your caravan

1108
01:28:34,320 --> 01:28:39,320
I want to chisel at my shortcomings
& become worthy of you

1109
01:28:40,320 --> 01:28:44,320
What should I do? What should I do?!

1110
01:29:08,790 --> 01:29:12,490
"I seek the truth that
pierces the darkest night..."

1111
01:29:12,950 --> 01:29:17,080
"I seek the devotion
I surrendered in your stead..."

1112
01:29:17,410 --> 01:29:20,120
"I have known the virtue
that surrender proffers..."'

1113
01:29:20,330 --> 01:29:23,490
"But I seek that heaven
for which I have bled.

1114
01:29:25,220 --> 01:29:30,220
From the day two strangers became
involved in love,

1115
01:29:31,220 --> 01:29:35,220
all the moments of loneliness have been delayed

1116
01:29:36,230 --> 01:29:43,230
Why do I want to fall in love once again?

1117
01:29:48,230 --> 01:29:53,230
My heart is looking for reasons to say no

1118
01:29:54,230 --> 01:29:59,230
But my body doesn't adhere to any bonds

1119
01:30:00,230 --> 01:30:02,230
Since I have met you

1120
01:30:03,230 --> 01:30:05,230
I want to rebel against my own self

1121
01:30:08,230 --> 01:30:13,230
I have fire left in me, come test it

1122
01:30:14,230 --> 01:30:18,230
I'm giving myself to you
so you do as you wish with me

1123
01:30:19,230 --> 01:30:24,230
O beloved...O beloved...

1124
01:31:30,830 --> 01:31:32,580
Is this supposed to be good?

1125
01:31:33,080 --> 01:31:34,700
I don't get it...

1126
01:31:36,910 --> 01:31:38,780
Didn't you say he was world famous?

1127
01:31:39,580 --> 01:31:40,700
He is...

1128
01:31:41,330 --> 01:31:44,530
People really admire his work...

1129
01:31:45,410 --> 01:31:46,830
And you?

1130
01:31:51,540 --> 01:31:52,780
You're awkward.

1131
01:31:54,580 --> 01:31:55,740
A little...

1132
01:32:00,200 --> 01:32:02,120
You can leave, if you like...

1133
01:32:02,790 --> 01:32:04,490
And leave you alone with him?

1134
01:32:05,660 --> 01:32:06,740
No way...

1135
01:32:06,910 --> 01:32:08,870
I'm dying to meet your ex-husband.

1136
01:32:13,910 --> 01:32:14,990
How come?

1137
01:32:16,330 --> 01:32:17,490
Just...

1138
01:32:21,790 --> 01:32:22,990
- Tahir...
- Hi...

1139
01:32:24,660 --> 01:32:28,240
Your Facebook tells me
too many things have changed...

1140
01:32:28,450 --> 01:32:30,030
Like the colour of your walls...

1141
01:32:30,540 --> 01:32:32,490
...and the claim to your heart...

1142
01:32:33,540 --> 01:32:34,410
Ayan.

1143
01:32:35,700 --> 01:32:36,620
Fantastic work, sir!

1144
01:32:36,740 --> 01:32:38,870
Sir? Really... Sir?!

1145
01:32:39,450 --> 01:32:42,030
Are you trying to
make me sound old?

1146
01:32:42,580 --> 01:32:45,410
By the way, he doesn"t
call you ma'am does he?

1147
01:32:45,580 --> 01:32:47,280
- You think?!
- I don't know!

1148
01:32:49,620 --> 01:32:53,160
So you're the one...
who's keeping her up at night...

1149
01:32:53,330 --> 01:32:55,700
Why waste time on sleep?

1150
01:32:56,330 --> 01:32:59,120
Sleep is critical...

1151
01:32:59,990 --> 01:33:02,030
...for her to dream about me?

1152
01:33:02,370 --> 01:33:03,700
Oh, now I definitely
won't let her sleep.

1153
01:33:03,790 --> 01:33:05,370
I can't see this...

1154
01:33:06,160 --> 01:33:07,780
Change of topic!

1155
01:33:09,540 --> 01:33:13,200
Besides, you've fulfilled
your dreams...

1156
01:33:13,410 --> 01:33:16,080
Your new work is very interesting.

1157
01:33:16,160 --> 01:33:17,870
Actually, fantastic!

1158
01:33:19,120 --> 01:33:23,700
Without a lover in his arms,
what else is a man to do...

1159
01:33:24,540 --> 01:33:28,660
- Do you guys rehearse these lines?
- No, totally natural!

1160
01:33:28,830 --> 01:33:30,080
Ah, natural...

1161
01:33:32,790 --> 01:33:36,780
People often shroud
their fear with words...

1162
01:33:37,700 --> 01:33:40,410
Our relationship
may have changed...

1163
01:33:41,620 --> 01:33:43,120
...but the fear remains.

1164
01:33:44,040 --> 01:33:45,240
Why did it change...

1165
01:33:45,790 --> 01:33:46,830
If I may ask?

1166
01:33:46,910 --> 01:33:49,780
Maybe you should
be asking the person...

1167
01:33:50,080 --> 01:33:52,160
...whose nights are now yours...

1168
01:33:54,330 --> 01:33:56,280
People often falter...

1169
01:33:57,120 --> 01:33:58,870
...on the slippery slopes
of relationships...

1170
01:33:59,540 --> 01:34:00,700
Yeah...

1171
01:34:03,200 --> 01:34:05,490
You could have shown
me a better way...

1172
01:34:06,290 --> 01:34:09,410
Let the one who is lost,
find his own way...

1173
01:34:15,700 --> 01:34:17,450
I hate you.

1174
01:34:17,540 --> 01:34:20,120
A little... no, a lot.

1175
01:34:20,830 --> 01:34:23,080
Such hatred... so soon?
Give me a chance...

1176
01:34:23,160 --> 01:34:26,660
Hating you is
completely justified...

1177
01:34:26,990 --> 01:34:29,950
Because I still love Saba...

1178
01:34:32,370 --> 01:34:34,660
I gave your love a chance...

1179
01:34:35,040 --> 01:34:38,120
It's time for you to
give my friendship a chance.

1180
01:34:39,490 --> 01:34:40,830
Isn't that hard?

1181
01:34:41,160 --> 01:34:42,160
- What?

1182
01:34:42,660 --> 01:34:46,370
To love someone...
who doesn't love you in return?

1183
01:34:51,160 --> 01:34:54,660
It's the most beautiful
feeling in the world...

1184
01:34:57,160 --> 01:35:00,030
- Doesn"t it make you feel weak?
- Not at all.

1185
01:35:01,120 --> 01:35:04,450
There's nothing like
the power of unrequited love...

1186
01:35:05,080 --> 01:35:08,410
Unlike other bonds,
it isn't shared...

1187
01:35:08,910 --> 01:35:11,530
It's mine...
and mine alone.

1188
01:35:14,870 --> 01:35:20,080
For a love like this,
I don't need Saba to love her...

1189
01:35:21,450 --> 01:35:23,660
There's no better love than that...

1190
01:35:26,700 --> 01:35:29,450
"'If you gamble in
the name of love...

1191
01:35:30,160 --> 01:35:32,950
"'Stake what you like...
what's to fear?"

1192
01:35:33,620 --> 01:35:35,990
"How wonderful if you win..."

1193
01:35:36,410 --> 01:35:41,080
"Even if you lose...
all is not lost.

1194
01:36:25,240 --> 01:36:26,740
Don't hang up!

1195
01:36:36,240 --> 01:36:38,280
Hello?

1196
01:36:38,370 --> 01:36:39,370
Shit!

1197
01:36:56,040 --> 01:36:57,780
- Hello?
- Ayan!

1198
01:36:58,910 --> 01:37:00,910
Where the hell are you?!

1199
01:37:01,080 --> 01:37:02,870
I've been trying to call you forever!

1200
01:37:02,990 --> 01:37:04,450
- You blocked my number!

1201
01:37:04,540 --> 01:37:05,700
What did you think I'd do?

1202
01:37:05,870 --> 01:37:07,080
Walk you down the aisle?

1203
01:37:07,910 --> 01:37:08,950
Did you marry him?

1204
01:37:11,120 --> 01:37:11,990
Yeah... I did.

1205
01:37:12,080 --> 01:37:13,490
Congratulations!

1206
01:37:14,580 --> 01:37:17,030
Now you're Mrs. DJ Ali!

1207
01:37:17,240 --> 01:37:20,370
Must be stuck on
him like headphones...

1208
01:37:21,200 --> 01:37:23,240
Ayan, stop your crap
before I hang up.

1209
01:37:23,450 --> 01:37:25,870
Hello!
You don't scare me!

1210
01:37:26,040 --> 01:37:27,200
Control yourself!

1211
01:37:27,660 --> 01:37:29,370
I have a girlfriend now.

1212
01:37:30,160 --> 01:37:32,740
She's really hot!

1213
01:37:33,200 --> 01:37:34,370
- And she writes poetry...

1214
01:37:34,450 --> 01:37:36,120
- You'll never get it!

1215
01:37:38,330 --> 01:37:39,490
Are you jealous?

1216
01:37:40,700 --> 01:37:42,200
- I think you're jealous.

1217
01:37:45,370 --> 01:37:46,740
No, dude...

1218
01:37:47,740 --> 01:37:51,700
I'm just really glad you called.

1219
01:37:51,910 --> 01:37:54,450
I'm so happy!

1220
01:37:56,740 --> 01:38:01,120
I have to go back
to my dinner date now...

1221
01:38:02,120 --> 01:38:05,370
- Candlelit... Romantic!

1222
01:38:05,620 --> 01:38:07,620
Ayan, listen...

1223
01:38:08,830 --> 01:38:10,490
I really missed you.

1224
01:38:12,740 --> 01:38:13,870
I hate you.

1225
01:38:15,080 --> 01:38:17,370
Okay...
But I missed you...

1226
01:38:20,490 --> 01:38:21,330
Bye.

1227
01:38:42,290 --> 01:38:44,580
'This is Saba... My girlfriend.'

1228
01:38:45,620 --> 01:38:46,280
'Wow...'

1229
01:38:46,740 --> 01:38:48,780
'What's she doing with you?!'

1230
01:38:48,870 --> 01:38:50,030
'She's gorgeous!'

1231
01:38:50,160 --> 01:38:52,200
'Yeah... Way better than you.'

1232
01:38:52,950 --> 01:38:54,450
- 'Like it’s a competition!'
- 'Of course it is!'

1233
01:38:54,830 --> 01:38:58,700
'Is DJ Ali still handsome
or did my curses work?'

1234
01:38:58,870 --> 01:39:00,200
'My prayers worked!

1235
01:39:00,540 --> 01:39:01,700
'Are you happy?

1236
01:39:05,490 --> 01:39:06,910
'Yeah... I'm happy.

1237
01:39:08,200 --> 01:39:10,330
"Feels like I'm finally
a part of Ali's life...'

1238
01:39:11,040 --> 01:39:13,410
'Our lives are wrapped in luggage...'

1239
01:39:14,540 --> 01:39:16,990
'And hotel rooms are home...'

1240
01:39:19,080 --> 01:39:20,280
'But it's nice.

1241
01:39:23,240 --> 01:39:26,240
"There's the occasional
dark cloud...'

1242
01:39:27,080 --> 01:39:29,030
'But other than that,
the sun is always shining.'

1243
01:39:30,580 --> 01:39:32,370
'I'm really, really happy.'

1244
01:39:33,740 --> 01:39:35,330
'I hate you.

1245
01:39:48,290 --> 01:39:50,240
'I'm coming to Vienna!'

1246
01:39:50,410 --> 01:39:51,660
'What plans?'

1247
01:39:52,700 --> 01:39:54,160
'I'm very busy...

1248
01:39:54,240 --> 01:39:56,330
'Meetings, appointments...'

1249
01:39:56,370 --> 01:39:57,870
'Shuddap! You're free!'

1250
01:39:58,200 --> 01:39:59,410
'Okay, I am!'

1251
01:39:59,490 --> 01:40:02,620
'Saba and I would
love to host you...'

1252
01:40:02,740 --> 01:40:04,950
'...but leave that DJ Ali behind.'

1253
01:40:05,080 --> 01:40:07,830
"He has a concert,
anyway... I'll be there!

1254
01:40:15,790 --> 01:40:17,200
- Hi!
- Hi!

1255
01:40:25,620 --> 01:40:28,450
You're dying to wait
by the window...

1256
01:40:29,120 --> 01:40:31,910
Check if she called...
Walk around restlessly...

1257
01:40:32,240 --> 01:40:34,950
You're not fooling
anyone with this pose...

1258
01:40:35,160 --> 01:40:37,330
What? Me? Why?
I'm totally chill...

1259
01:40:37,410 --> 01:40:38,660
I'm cool!

1260
01:40:39,620 --> 01:40:41,410
Someone's at the door...

1261
01:40:42,580 --> 01:40:44,200
Go... She's here.

1262
01:40:50,370 --> 01:40:51,450
Hi!

1263
01:40:51,620 --> 01:40:52,580
Ayan!

1264
01:40:52,700 --> 01:40:54,370
Hi... Cold outside?

1265
01:40:55,490 --> 01:40:56,700
What are you doing?

1266
01:40:56,990 --> 01:40:59,160
Didn't bring any wine?
Flowers? Thorns? Nothing?

1267
01:40:59,240 --> 01:41:00,120
Should I have?

1268
01:41:00,200 --> 01:41:01,280
Saba!

1269
01:41:01,830 --> 01:41:02,580
Alizeh.

1270
01:41:04,290 --> 01:41:05,450
Welcome home...

1271
01:41:05,620 --> 01:41:07,240
- So Alizeh...
- So nice to meet you...

1272
01:41:07,330 --> 01:41:09,950
Heard so much about you...
All good things, I hope!

1273
01:41:11,540 --> 01:41:12,580
What...?

1274
01:41:12,660 --> 01:41:16,330
No... just... trying to
ease the tension!

1275
01:41:16,580 --> 01:41:17,870
Get a hold on yourself...

1276
01:41:17,950 --> 01:41:20,740
The "tension' will disappear?
Come...

1277
01:41:20,950 --> 01:41:23,580
- You know how girls can be!
- Sexist remark...

1278
01:41:23,700 --> 01:41:26,030
- Not appreciated!
- Not at all!

1279
01:41:26,200 --> 01:41:29,410
Give our intelligence its due!

1280
01:41:32,080 --> 01:41:32,990
Wine?

1281
01:41:33,080 --> 01:41:34,370
Maybe later...

1282
01:41:34,450 --> 01:41:35,530
Ah, okay...

1283
01:41:35,620 --> 01:41:36,780
But, Saba...

1284
01:41:36,870 --> 01:41:40,780
Beauty like yours often
overshadows intelligence...

1285
01:41:41,080 --> 01:41:44,030
Ask those of us who
live off our personality...

1286
01:41:44,160 --> 01:41:46,120
Beauty fades, Alizeh...

1287
01:41:46,330 --> 01:41:48,950
But Death, himself,
can't kill personality...

1288
01:41:49,240 --> 01:41:52,830
Wow... So the poetry
really was yours!

1289
01:41:53,080 --> 01:41:57,240
I thought Ayan was just
copying it off the internet!

1290
01:41:58,660 --> 01:42:00,580
If it weren't for poetry...

1291
01:42:00,910 --> 01:42:03,410
...I'd have died a thousand
living deaths already...

1292
01:42:05,330 --> 01:42:06,330
Cheese?

1293
01:42:09,950 --> 01:42:14,080
Will I sound phony
if I praise you some more?

1294
01:42:14,580 --> 01:42:16,700
Not at all...
Please go ahead...

1295
01:42:16,790 --> 01:42:18,080
No judgments!

1296
01:42:18,620 --> 01:42:20,200
Pictures do you no justice...

1297
01:42:20,290 --> 01:42:22,490
You're even more
beautiful in person.

1298
01:42:24,660 --> 01:42:28,200
Oh, so those pictures
were to show you...

1299
01:42:29,240 --> 01:42:31,280
To make her jealous...

1300
01:42:31,740 --> 01:42:33,700
...but why waste
envy on the resentful?

1301
01:42:34,240 --> 01:42:35,120
Wow, Ayan...

1302
01:42:35,200 --> 01:42:37,030
Saba, looks like you've
had an influence...

1303
01:42:37,330 --> 01:42:38,200
A little bit of it...

1304
01:42:38,290 --> 01:42:39,450
A little to go...

1305
01:42:43,620 --> 01:42:45,080
Well, it's not envy...

1306
01:42:45,330 --> 01:42:47,780
But you can’t sing
to a mute person....

1307
01:42:47,870 --> 01:42:49,660
...and expect them
not to feel inferior!

1308
01:42:51,700 --> 01:42:55,990
Speaking of singing...
This is my favourite song...

1309
01:42:56,200 --> 01:43:00,030
"'O lover, don't ask me
to love like I did before..."

1310
01:43:00,700 --> 01:43:02,870
"'O lover, don't ask me..."

1311
01:43:03,290 --> 01:43:04,830
To love like I did before.

1312
01:43:15,200 --> 01:43:15,910
Dinner?

1313
01:43:16,580 --> 01:43:17,240
Bread?

1314
01:43:23,620 --> 01:43:24,950
Why didn't you bring Ali?

1315
01:43:26,080 --> 01:43:28,120
He had a concert... so...

1316
01:43:28,490 --> 01:43:30,410
DJ Ali's super busy, you see...

1317
01:43:32,080 --> 01:43:35,200
Why do you keep calling him that?
Like it's an insult...

1318
01:43:35,330 --> 01:43:36,620
Not at all!

1319
01:43:37,040 --> 01:43:40,950
Who doesn"t dream of making
people dance on their fingertips?

1320
01:43:43,160 --> 01:43:45,240
Alizeh, may I ask
you something personal?

1321
01:43:45,330 --> 01:43:47,080
If you don't mind...

1322
01:43:47,370 --> 01:43:48,740
Sure...

1323
01:43:50,240 --> 01:43:54,030
How did you not fall in love
with someone so charming?

1324
01:44:00,290 --> 01:44:01,990
Charming for you, maybe...

1325
01:44:02,200 --> 01:44:04,660
He was a big baby
when I met him...

1326
01:44:05,330 --> 01:44:09,490
He cried on the streets,
cried in my arms...

1327
01:44:09,580 --> 01:44:10,910
Really?!

1328
01:44:11,490 --> 01:44:15,160
Ayan... Is this a compliment
or a slight?

1329
01:44:15,450 --> 01:44:17,410
You've never cried in my arms...

1330
01:44:18,540 --> 01:44:20,870
How could I cry in your arms...

1331
01:44:22,290 --> 01:44:24,740
...when I'm so distracted by
my other feelings...

1332
01:45:08,580 --> 01:45:10,530
You got lucky, Ayan!

1333
01:45:11,330 --> 01:45:13,660
Saba's wonderful.

1334
01:45:21,240 --> 01:45:22,200
Anyway...

1335
01:45:22,950 --> 01:45:24,530
- Thank you for dinner.
- Go to hell!

1336
01:45:25,200 --> 01:45:27,120
'Thank you for dinner'?!

1337
01:45:29,790 --> 01:45:30,910
You're soulless!

1338
01:45:31,450 --> 01:45:33,240
Don't you have any feelings?!

1339
01:45:33,870 --> 01:45:35,950
Not jealousy, not guilt...

1340
01:45:36,240 --> 01:45:39,330
- Nothing?!
- I feel everything, Ayan!

1341
01:45:40,120 --> 01:45:41,910
But you’d never
understand if I told you...

1342
01:45:41,990 --> 01:45:43,490
You'd just misconstrue it all!

1343
01:45:44,990 --> 01:45:46,530
You're a goddamn child!

1344
01:45:46,790 --> 01:45:48,280
You've got everything!

1345
01:45:48,740 --> 01:45:51,160
Goals, passion,
a relationship...

