It's my greatest strength.

1607
02:15:53,540 --> 02:15:55,910
Love is my weakness...

1608
02:15:56,580 --> 02:15:58,700
Why don't you understand that?

1609
02:15:58,950 --> 02:16:03,660
Because a man and a woman
cannot be just friends!

1610
02:16:15,040 --> 02:16:16,990
Go...

1611
02:16:17,160 --> 02:16:18,780
Get out of here...

1612
02:16:19,490 --> 02:16:20,740
Go.

1613
02:16:20,910 --> 02:16:24,160
I can't explain this to you anymore...

1614
02:16:24,240 --> 02:16:27,660
If you can't understand, just leave...

1615
02:16:27,910 --> 02:16:31,120
Take your stuff and get out!

1616
02:16:32,790 --> 02:16:33,870
Get out!

1617
02:16:33,990 --> 02:16:35,660
Get out, Ayan!

1618
02:16:42,830 --> 02:16:43,910
Alizeh...

1619
02:16:45,910 --> 02:16:47,330
Alizeh, I'm sorry...

1620
02:16:58,580 --> 02:17:01,450
It’s a strange story...
of Love and Friendship.

1621
02:17:01,950 --> 02:17:04,660
Love, the hero...
and Friendship, the heroine.

1622
02:17:05,120 --> 02:17:08,200
The awful thing is that
Love never understood Friendship.

1623
02:17:08,410 --> 02:17:12,740
'I do love you, Ayan...
Just not the way you want me to.

1624
02:17:13,040 --> 02:17:14,870
- 'Love is passion...'

1625
02:17:15,700 --> 02:17:18,780
- '...but friendship is peace.'

1626
02:17:21,740 --> 02:17:26,330
One night, tired and weary,
Love threw a tantrum...

1627
02:17:27,120 --> 02:17:28,700
Like a spoilt child... Stupid!

1628
02:17:29,080 --> 02:17:30,910
And what did Friendship do?

1629
02:17:32,910 --> 02:17:33,870
Alizeh...

1630
02:17:34,240 --> 02:17:37,330
Friendship threw a tantrum, too,
and left in a huff.

1631
02:17:40,950 --> 02:17:43,080
And where else do heroines go?

1632
02:17:43,870 --> 02:17:44,780
The airport.

1633
02:17:45,290 --> 02:17:48,120
- 'Ayan... I'm going back home...'

1634
02:17:48,410 --> 02:17:50,490
And Love freaked out...

1635
02:17:50,660 --> 02:17:54,280
- 'I hope one day you’ll
understand my love...

1636
02:17:54,580 --> 02:17:58,280
When Love realised that Friendship
is leaving him forever... He ran.

1637
02:17:58,660 --> 02:18:01,450
And how he ran!

1638
02:18:06,490 --> 02:18:07,370
In taxis...

1639
02:18:07,580 --> 02:18:08,620
Heathrow Airport!

1640
02:18:11,660 --> 02:18:12,740
In trains...

1641
02:18:16,950 --> 02:18:18,410
He ran!

1642
02:18:21,120 --> 02:18:23,030
He didn't stop to breathe...

1643
02:18:24,330 --> 02:18:28,030
Because Love knew...
Friendship was about to breathe her last...

1644
02:18:29,080 --> 02:18:32,330
And he wanted to be with
her 'til her last moments.

1645
02:18:33,120 --> 02:18:34,450
That was Love's right.

1646
02:18:45,620 --> 02:18:47,950
I need to get to BA 1 09!

1647
02:18:49,660 --> 02:18:51,990
I'm sorry, the gate closed
20 minutes ago!

1648
02:18:52,080 --> 02:18:53,530
Has the flight taken off?

1649
02:18:53,700 --> 02:18:55,030
It's about to go!

1650
02:19:02,040 --> 02:19:03,410
- Hello?
- Alizeh!

1651
02:19:03,620 --> 02:19:05,620
I'm at the airport!
I'm here!

1652
02:19:05,950 --> 02:19:07,740
Please don't go Alizeh, please stay!

1653
02:19:09,790 --> 02:19:12,330
Ayan, I'm taking off.

1654
02:19:53,200 --> 02:19:54,030
Hello?

1655
02:20:29,080 --> 02:20:30,030
Alizeh...

1656
02:20:31,240 --> 02:20:33,490
You can't die...

1657
02:20:38,620 --> 02:20:40,580
- Ma'am, keep that oxygen mask on.

1658
02:20:40,660 --> 02:20:43,740
Alizeh, listen to him...
Put it back.

1659
02:20:46,790 --> 02:20:48,160
Ayan...

1660
02:20:49,700 --> 02:20:52,330
I'm acting, I'm not really dying...

1661
02:20:52,740 --> 02:20:55,330
Don't react... We'll get caught.

1662
02:21:02,410 --> 02:21:05,370
How else do you runaway
from a runway?

1663
02:21:06,240 --> 02:21:09,030
Cancer's got to have some perks...

1664
02:21:14,830 --> 02:21:17,330
You came to the airport, Ayan...

1665
02:21:18,740 --> 02:21:21,410
You fulfilled my dream!

1666
02:21:23,160 --> 02:21:25,870
Alizeh, I'm sorry for last night...

1667
02:21:28,160 --> 02:21:32,280
Friendship doesn't know
sorry's and thank you's...

1668
02:21:36,580 --> 02:21:40,660
I swear I'll never trouble
you about this again...

1669
02:21:41,790 --> 02:21:43,530
Because, Ayan...

1670
02:21:44,370 --> 02:21:48,160
It's a lot like love!

1671
02:22:12,290 --> 02:22:14,700
Come, now, sing something...

1672
02:22:15,200 --> 02:22:17,910
Anything you like... I'm sick!

1673
02:22:39,080 --> 02:22:41,160
Hey... can I sing something?

1674
02:22:53,260 --> 02:22:55,260
In your presence,

1675
02:22:56,200 --> 02:22:58,200
...if I'm not there...

1676
02:22:59,200 --> 02:23:03,200
...there is no sadness!

1677
02:23:04,200 --> 02:23:10,200
Stories of us, & of our closeness...

1678
02:23:11,200 --> 02:23:14,200
...aren't any less than others!

1679
02:23:15,210 --> 02:23:20,210
So many times I have turned,

1680
02:23:21,210 --> 02:23:25,270
my mornings into evenings sitting in your courtyard.

1681
02:23:26,220 --> 02:23:34,610
Oh my moon...
Oh my beloved moon.

1682
02:23:37,170 --> 02:23:43,170
Oh my moon, my beloved moon
O my love...

1683
02:25:33,100 --> 02:25:37,100
I have done my share in loving someone

1684
02:25:38,100 --> 02:25:43,100
Even when you were there,
when we were together

1685
02:25:44,100 --> 02:25:48,100
To tell you the truth, I loved you...

1686
02:25:49,110 --> 02:25:53,110
...more than you did yourself,
even after you left.

1687
02:25:55,110 --> 02:25:59,110
I am the pain,

1688
02:26:00,110 --> 02:26:05,110
You're the cure, no?

1689
02:26:06,110 --> 02:26:10,110
I am the fire,

1690
02:26:11,110 --> 02:26:17,110
and you're the wind
(that gives rise to the fire)

1691
02:26:18,110 --> 02:26:20,110
Ali, Ali, Ali, Alizeh

1692
02:26:22,710 --> 02:26:24,110
Where are you?

1693
02:26:25,510 --> 02:26:28,110
You're there in my heart, no?

1694
02:26:33,110 --> 02:26:36,110
I'm yours!

1695
02:26:36,120 --> 02:26:39,120
You remember, no?

1696
02:27:12,120 --> 02:27:17,120
When the sun goes down, it feels like...

1697
02:27:18,120 --> 02:27:22,120
...your head is there on my shoulder.

1698
02:27:23,120 --> 02:27:28,120
Wherever I end up staying...

1699
02:27:29,120 --> 02:27:33,120
...in my memories, your home is there

1700
02:27:55,120 --> 02:28:05,120
Wherever I am, you are there, no?

1701
02:28:06,120 --> 02:28:16,120
I'm the fire, and you the wind, no?
